This paper involves the use of computational dynamic social network analysis (CDSNA) to study the similarities and differences in the online populations of two neighboring provinces in the Philippines. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Other possible sub-categories include cs.SD (Software Development), cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), as the paper also touches on topics related to online privacy, livelihood, and gender and age dynamics in social networks.
